A huge [explosion](http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-15705948) at a
military base near Iran's capital Tehran, killed at least 17 soldiers
including one high-ranking Revolutionary Guard official on November 12, 2011.

According to official sources the blast occurred when weapons were being moved
inside a Revolutionary Guards depot. Windows in nearby buildings were
shattered and the blast was heard in Tehran, 40 km (25 miles) away.

[![Image by takseda1385.blogspot.com](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2011/11/blast.jpg)](http://takseda1385.blogspot.com/2011/11/blog-
post.html)

Image by takseda1385.blogspot.com

Several Iranian bloggers reacted to this explosion amid [rising tension
between Iran and
Israel](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2011/11/08/iranbloggers-react-to-
military-strikes-rumors/) on its nuclear program.

Na Aram[
writes](http://noreasonfor.wordpress.com/2011/11/12/%D8%B5%D8%AF%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%81%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%B4%D8%AF%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%AA%D9%87%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%88-%D8%AD%D9%88%D9%85%D9%87/)
[fa] that the blast made several buildings tremble in Tehran.

Tahririeh Khamoush [published](http://takseda1385.blogspot.com/2011/11/blog-
post.html) a photo of the explosion and
[writes](http://takseda1385.blogspot.com/2011/11/blog-post_12.html) [fa]:

> The blast happened at the same time at three different military bases, but
> the Revolutionary Guards just want to say it was one explosion… Do not
> forget Malarad [where official reports say the blast occurred] is a depot
> for [ Shahab 3](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shahab-3) missiles.

Ta Azadi
[writes](http://taazadi.wordpress.com/2011/11/12/%D9%87%D9%86%D9%88%D8%B2-%D8%AC%D9%86%DA%AF-%D9%86%D8%B4%D8%AF%D9%87-%D8%AA%D9%84%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF%DB%8C%D9%85/)
[fa]:

> We've lost lives before a war has even started. Instead of frightening the
> enemy they [the Revolutionary Guard] has panicked our people. I am afraid if
> war breaks out, what will we do with these people who so easily lost these
> lives?… and nobody takes responsibility.

Harfayi az tahe del [says ](http://darazarehbin.blogspot.com/2011/11/blog-
post_12.html) [fa]:

> Today's explosions are very suspicious and the Islamic Republic does not
> inform us in an appropriate way. There were three explosions and it is very
> hard to imagine them happening accidentally.

Mola Hassani [writes](http://mollah.blogspot.com/2011/11/blog-post_12.html)
[fa]:

> They who can not protect their own weapons depot, how could they defend the
> nuclear facilities from being attacked?

